wikipedia_page.main: Oswald Charles Baker (1915–2004) was a sedevacantist Roman Catholic priest who lived in Downham Market in Norfolk.

response: * Father Oswald Baker, an English priest who was a sedevacantist by at least 1982, and reportedly some time prior to that.
* Oswald Baker (1915–2004), controversial Catholic priest, originally at St Dominic, Downham Market and later had his own chapel.
